Parliament, Tuesday, 28 February 2023 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts will tomorrow hold a hearing with the South African Broadcasting Corporation (SABC) on its annual report and financial statements for the 2021/22 financial year as well as investigations, irregular, fruitless and wasteful expenditures.  Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Wednesday, 1 March 2023 Time: 09:30 Venue: Committee Room M314, Third Floor, Marks Building.  Please note that this will only be a physical meeting.  ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES.  For media enquiries, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze Parliamentary Communication Services Tel: 021 403 8268 Cell: 081 377 0686 Email: fndenze@parliament.gov.za Committees have the power to summons any person to appear before them to give evidence or produce documents. They may ask any person or institution to report to them and may receive petitions, representations or submissions from the public. They play a crucial role in the law-making process. Economic Freedom Fighters on the provincial list for the province of Gauteng